-- Albaraka Turk signs murabaha loan deal worth $221 mln
-- 
-- Tue Sep 23, 2014 08:14AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 23 (Reuters) - Turkish participation bank Albaraka Turk <ALBRK.IS> said on Tuesday it had signed a one-year murabaha loan deal worth $151 million and 54.4 million euro ($70.17 million).

The bank, a unit of Bahrain-based Al Baraka Banking Group <BARKA.BH>, said cost of the loan was Libor, Euribor + 110 basis points.